      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offering a museum-grade 2002 BMW M3, a definitive example of the E46 chassis. This specimen features the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six, utilizing six individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS variable valve timing for linear power delivery up to its 8,000 RPM redline. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise 6-speed Getrag manual transmission and an M-Variable limited-slip differential. Critical preventive maintenance has been performed, including a comprehensive subframe reinforcement and rod bearing replacement. The suspension geometry remains factory-spec with refreshed bushings, ensuring the original handling dynamics are preserved. Finished in pristine original paint with no bolster wear on the Nappa leather interior, this is a turn-key investment for the discerning collector.",
